d, Verenigd Koninkrijk","England":"England"},"en":{"Abt 1124–Aft 1166":"about 1124–after 1166","1124–1166":"1124–1166","1125–Female":"1125–Deceased","1146–Male":"1146–Deceased","1154–Female":"1154–Deceased","1094–1142":"1094–1142","Abt 1124":"about 1124","1125":"1125","Aft 1166":"after 1166","1146":"1146","1124":"1124","ABT 1146":"about 1146","1166":"1166","1154":"1154","1142":"1142","Aft 1142":"after 1142","1094":"1094",", LINCOLNSHIRE, ENGLAND":"Lincolnshire, England, United Kingdom","England":"England","nameMeanings":[{"name":"Veer","type":"LAST","attribution":"Dictionary of Family Names in Britain and Ireland © University of the West of England 2016","meanings":["English:  see  Vere  ."],"variants":[{"name":"Vere","meanings":["English (of Norman origin): habitational name, mostly from Vair in Ancenis, named with Gaulish <i>ver(n)-</i> ‘alder’. This was the probable home in the 11th century of the Breton lord Aubrey (Albericus) de Ver, who followed William the Conqueror to England and founded an influential family who held the earldom of Oxford until 1703. In a few cases the surname could be from other places in France, such as Ver in Manche and Calvados, which have the same etymology as Vair.","French (mainy Vendée; <b>Veré</b>): variant of <b>Vairé</b>, from Old French <i>vairie</i> ‘variegated, spotted’, applied as a nickname for someone who has freckles."]}]},{"name":"Guy","type":"FIRST","attribution":"Dictionary of First Names © Patrick Hanks and Flavia Hodges 1990, 2003, 2006.","meanings":["From an Old French name, of Germanic (Frankish) origin, originally a short form of a compound name starting with <i>witu</i> ‘wood’ or <i>wīt</i> ‘wide’. This was adopted by the Normans and introduced by them to England. In Old French initial <i>w-</i> regularly became <i>gu-</i>. The usual Norman forms of the name were <i>Gy</i> or <i>Guido</i>. In medieval Latin the same name is found as <i>Wido</i>. It was a popular name among the Normans, enhanced no doubt by the romance of Guy of Warwick, recounting the exploits of a folk hero of the Crusades."],"variants":[]}],"lifeSummary":"Guy Veer was born about 1124, in England as the son of Guy Veer. He had at least 1 son with Mrs Guy De Vere. He died after 1166."},"et":{"Abt 1124–Aft 1166":"umbes 1124–pärast 1166","1124–1166":"1124–1166","1125–Female":"1125–Surnud","1146–Male":"1146–Surnud","1154–Female":"1154–Surnud","1094–1142":"1094–1142","Abt 1124":"umbes 1124","1125":"1125","Aft 1166":"pärast 1166","1146":"1146","1124":"1124","ABT 1146":"umbes 1146","1166":"1166","1154":"1154","1142":"1142","Aft 1142":"pärast 1142","1094":"1094",", LINCOLNSHIRE, ENGLAND":"Lincolnshire, Inglismaa, United Kingdom","England":"England"},"fi":{"Abt 1124–Aft 1166":"noin 1124–1166 jälkeen","1124–1166":"1124–1166","1125–Female":"1125–Kuollut","1146–Male":"1146–Kuollut","1154–Female":"1154–Kuollut","1094–1142":"1094–1142","Abt 1124":"noin 1124","1125":"1125","Aft 1166":"1166 jälkeen","1146":"1146","1124":"1124","ABT 1146":"noin 1146","1166":"1166","1154":"1154","1142":"1142","Aft 1142":"1142 jälkeen","1094":"1094",", LINCOLNSHIRE, ENGLAND":"Lincolnshire, Englanti, Yhdistynyt kuningaskunta","England":"England"},"fr":{"Abt 1124–Aft 1166":"environ 1124–après 1166","1124–1166":"1124–1166","1125–Female":"1125–Décédée","1146–Male":"1146–Décédé","1154–Female":"1154–Décédée","1094–1142":"1094–1142","Abt 1124":"environ 1124","1125":"1125","Aft 1166":"après 1166","1146":"1146","1124":"1124","ABT 1146":"environ 1146","1166":"1166","1154":"1154","1142":"1142","Aft 1142":"après 1142","1094":"1094",", LINCOLNSHIRE, ENGLAND":"Lincolnshire, Angleterre, Royaume-Uni","England":"Angleterre","lifeSummary":"Guy Veer est né environ 1124, à Angleterre, fils de Guy Veer. Il a eu au moins 1 fils avec Mrs Guy De Vere. Il est décédé après 1166."},"de":{"Abt 1124–Aft 1166":"um 1124–nach 1166","1124–1166":"1124–1166","1125–Female":"1125–Verstorben","1146–Male":"1146–Verstorben","1154–Female":"1154–Verstorben","1094–1142":"1094–1142","A